## How This Works on a Server in the Future

Right now on your laptop:
```
klist shows tickets = Windows is already 
logged into Kerberos automatically
because you're on a corporate laptop
```

On a server it works differently:
```
Server doesn't have a logged-in user
        ↓
Keytab file acts as an 
"automatic password file" for Kerberos
        ↓
Application uses keytab to get 
Kerberos tickets without human login
```

Think of it like this:

| Environment | How Kerberos Authenticates |
|---|---|
| Your laptop | Uses YOUR windows login automatically |
| Server/Production | Uses the **keytab file** to authenticate automatically |

This is exactly why you have the keytab file — it's the server's equivalent of your Windows login. ✅

